---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Vibe Readiness Review — VibeFlare.ai"
  description="A one-time security audit for vibe-coded apps. We check authentication, data access, exposed secrets, and API security — then tell you exactly what to fix before a breach does."
>

  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 scan-line pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 h-[500px] w-[700px] rounded-full bg-vf-accent/5 blur-[120px] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pt-24 pb-16 md:pt-32 md:pb-20">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted mb-8">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-vf-white transition-colors">VibeFlare</a>
        <span class="text-vf-border">/</span>
        <a href="/#services" class="hover:text-vf-white transition-colors">Services</a>
        <span class="text-vf-border">/</span>
        <span class="text-vf-text">Readiness Review</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-vf-amber/40 bg-vf-amber/5 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-mono text-vf-amber mb-6">
            <span class="inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-vf-amber"></span>
            One-time audit · Flat $300
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-[1.08] font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">
            Vibe Readiness<br />
            <span class="gradient-text">Review.</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">
            A structured security audit of your vibe-coded app. We go through everything an attacker would look for — then tell you exactly what's exposed, what's broken, and what to fix first.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">
            You get a clear verdict: <span class="text-vf-teal font-medium">ship</span> or <span class="text-vf-pink font-medium">don't ship</span> — plus the prioritized fix list to get there.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start gap-4">
            <a
              href="#get-started"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-vf-accent px-6 py-3 text-base font-medium text-white hover:bg-vf-accent-light transition-colors glow-accent"
            >
              <span class="inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-vf-teal animate-pulse-slow"></span>
              Request a Review — $300
            </a>
            <a href="#what-we-check" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-vf-border px-6 py-3 text-base font-medium text-vf-text hover:border-vf-muted transition-colors">
              See what's included
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Terminal mock -->
        <div class="hidden lg:block">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel overflow-hidden">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-3 border-b border-vf-border/50 bg-vf-dark">
              <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-vf-red/70"></span>
              <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-vf-amber/70"></span>
              <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-vf-teal/70"></span>
              <span class="ml-3 text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted">vibeflare — readiness-scan</span>
            </div>
            <div class="p-5 font-mono text-xs space-y-2.5">
              <p class="text-vf-muted">$ vibeflare scan --app your-lovable-app</p>
              <p class="text-vf-muted">→ Connecting to project...</p>
              <div class="pt-1 space-y-2">
                <p class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span class="text-vf-pink font-semibold">CRITICAL</span>
                  <span class="text-vf-text">Supabase service_role key exposed in JS bundle</span>
                </p>
                <p class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span class="text-vf-pink font-semibold">CRITICAL</span>
                  <span class="text-vf-text">RLS disabled on users table — all rows readable</span>
                </p>
                <p class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span class="text-vf-amber font-semibold">WARN&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                  <span class="text-vf-text">No rate limiting on /api/auth/login</span>
                </p>
                <p class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span class="text-vf-amber font-semibold">WARN&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                  <span class="text-vf-text">Stripe key readable from client-side code</span>
                </p>
                <p class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span class="text-vf-amber font-semibold">WARN&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                  <span class="text-vf-text">Admin routes lack auth verification</span>
                </p>
                <p class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span class="text-vf-teal font-semibold">PASS&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                  <span class="text-vf-muted">SQL injection (parameterized queries detected)</span>
                </p>
                <p class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <span class="text-vf-teal font-semibold">PASS&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>
                  <span class="text-vf-muted">HTTPS enforced on all routes</span>
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="pt-2 border-t border-vf-border/50">
                <p class="text-vf-pink font-semibold">VERDICT: Do not ship. 2 critical issues require immediate fix.</p>
                <p class="text-vf-muted mt-1">Full report → readiness-report-2025.pdf</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CONTEXT STRIP ============ -->
  <section class="border-t border-vf-border/50 bg-vf-dark">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-10">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-0 md:divide-x divide-vf-border/50 text-center">
        <div class="px-8">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold font-mono text-vf-pink">45%</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-vf-muted">of AI-generated code introduces critical vulnerabilities</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs font-mono text-vf-border">Veracode, 2025</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-8">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold font-mono text-vf-amber">1 in 5</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-vf-muted">vibe-coded apps have serious, exploitable security gaps</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs font-mono text-vf-border">Wiz Research, 2025</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-8">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold font-mono text-vf-teal">48 hrs</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-vf-muted">typical turnaround from access to full written report</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs font-mono text-vf-border">VibeFlare SLA</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ WHAT WE CHECK ============ -->
  <section id="what-we-check" class="border-t border-vf-border/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mb-14">
        <p class="text-sm font-mono text-vf-amber uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">What We Check</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">
          The six areas where vibe-coded apps break.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-vf-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
          These aren't hypothetical risks. They're the exact vulnerabilities found in thousands of live apps built on Lovable, Replit, Cursor, and Bolt — confirmed by independent security research.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-pink/40 text-vf-pink font-mono font-bold text-sm">01</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Authentication</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">Can someone access your app without logging in? Can they log in as someone else? AI-built auth is frequently bypassable through client-side tricks or undocumented API routes.</p>
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Login and signup flow verification</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Route protection on authenticated pages</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Session handling and token expiry</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Password reset flow integrity</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-pink/40 text-vf-pink font-mono font-bold text-sm">02</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Data Access Rules</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">The most common failure in Supabase-backed apps: Row-Level Security exists but doesn't actually restrict anything. User A can read User B's data. We verify your rules enforce what they claim to enforce.</p>
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Supabase RLS policy correctness (not just existence)</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Cross-user data access testing</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Admin vs. user privilege separation</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Database direct-access exposure</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-amber/40 text-vf-amber font-mono font-bold text-sm">03</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Exposed Credentials</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">API keys, database passwords, and Stripe keys baked into frontend code are readable by anyone who views source. In 400+ confirmed cases, Supabase service keys were found in JavaScript bundles of live apps.</p>
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Frontend bundle secrets scan</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Environment variable configuration audit</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> API key scope and permission review</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Third-party integration credential hygiene</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-amber/40 text-vf-amber font-mono font-bold text-sm">04</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">API &amp; Endpoint Security</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">AI-generated APIs frequently skip the basics: no authentication checks, no limits on how many requests someone can make, no validation of what gets sent in. These are the entry points attackers go to first.</p>
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Unauthenticated endpoint enumeration</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Abuse protection (login, signup, contact)</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Input validation and injection risk</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Admin and internal API exposure</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-border/80 text-vf-muted font-mono font-bold text-sm">05</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Infrastructure Configuration</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">Default settings on Vercel, Supabase, and Firebase are often not production-safe. We check that your deployment environment isn't leaving doors open by default.</p>
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Vercel / Netlify config and preview protection</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> HTTPS enforcement and redirect checks</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Storage bucket and asset access settings</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Platform security defaults review</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-border/80 text-vf-muted font-mono font-bold text-sm">06</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Third-Party Integrations</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">Stripe, Resend, OpenAI, Clerk — every integration is a new surface. We check that webhooks are verified, keys are scoped correctly, and integrations can't be abused to trigger unintended charges or data access.</p>
              <div class="space-y-1.5">
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Webhook signature verification</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> Payment flow integrity (Stripe)</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> AI API key exposure and cost injection risk</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-vf-muted flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-vf-border">→</span> OAuth and SSO configuration</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ WHAT YOU GET ============ -->
  <section class="border-t border-vf-border/50 bg-vf-dark">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mb-14">
        <p class="text-sm font-mono text-vf-teal uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">What You Get</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">
          A report you can act on. Not a spreadsheet of problems.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-vf-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Security audits are only useful if you know what to do next. Every Readiness Review delivers four things.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

        <div class="flex gap-5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel/50">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full bg-vf-accent/10 border border-vf-accent/30 text-vf-accent text-sm font-mono font-bold">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Ship / Don't Ship Verdict</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">A clear, unambiguous call on whether your app is safe to go live. No hedging. If there's a critical issue blocking launch, we say so directly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel/50">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full bg-vf-accent/10 border border-vf-accent/30 text-vf-accent text-sm font-mono font-bold">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Prioritized Fix List</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">Every finding is labeled Critical, Warning, or Informational — with plain-language explanations of the risk and specific instructions for fixing it. You know what to do first and why.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel/50">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full bg-vf-accent/10 border border-vf-accent/30 text-vf-accent text-sm font-mono font-bold">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">Written Report</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">A structured PDF you can share with investors, enterprise customers, or your co-founder. Documents what was checked, what was found, and your security posture at time of audit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-5 p-6 rounded-xl border border-vf-border bg-vf-panel/50">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full bg-vf-accent/10 border border-vf-accent/30 text-vf-accent text-sm font-mono font-bold">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">30-Minute Debrief Call</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">We walk through the report together. Ask any question. Most founders leave knowing exactly what they'll fix and in what order.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ HOW IT WORKS ============ -->
  <section class="border-t border-vf-border/50">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mb-14">
        <p class="text-sm font-mono text-vf-accent uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">How It Works</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight font-[family-name:var(--font-display)]">
          Four steps. Typically done in 48 hours.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-vf-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
          We've kept this as simple as possible. You don't need to understand security to go through it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="relative">
        <div class="hidden md:block absolute top-8 left-8 right-8 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-vf-amber/30 via-vf-accent/30 to-vf-teal/30"></div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">

          <div class="relative bg-vf-panel rounded-xl border border-vf-border p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-amber/40 bg-vf-dark text-vf-amber font-mono font-bold text-sm mb-4 relative z-10">
              01
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">You book and share access</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">Submit your project details and give us read access to your repo and platform. We'll send a checklist of exactly what we need — nothing more.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="relative bg-vf-panel rounded-xl border border-vf-border p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-accent/40 bg-vf-dark text-vf-accent font-mono font-bold text-sm mb-4 relative z-10">
              02
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">We run the audit</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">We manually test and review all six areas within 48 business hours. No automated scan-and-send. A human goes through your app.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="relative bg-vf-panel rounded-xl border border-vf-border p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-accent/40 bg-vf-dark text-vf-accent font-mono font-bold text-sm mb-4 relative z-10">
              03
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">You receive the report</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">Written findings land in your inbox. Verdict up front, full detail below. Everything explained in plain language — no security jargon.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="relative bg-vf-panel rounded-xl border border-vf-teal/20 p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-center h-10 w-10 rounded-full border border-vf-teal/40 bg-vf-dark text-vf-teal font-mono font-bold text-sm mb-4 relative z-10">
              04
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-vf-text font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-2">We debrief together</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-vf-muted leading-relaxed">30-minute call to walk through what we found. Ask anything. Most founders leave knowing exactly what they'll fix and in what order.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ RIGHT FOR YOU IF ============ -->
  <section class="border-t border-vf-border/50 bg-vf-dark">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">

        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-mono text-vf-teal uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">This Is Right For You If</p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] mb-8">
            You built something people are actually using.
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-vf-teal mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">&#x2713;</span>
              <p class="text-sm text-vf-muted">You built with Lovable, Replit, Cursor, Bolt, or Firebase Studio</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
